ly</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Since this morning, the pet that was previously lvl 42, now is at least lvl 58.<br>
<br>
Any idea if this is a mistake or intended by verant ?<br>
<br>
I will check later the dommage output and HP of the pet.<br>
<br>
Do you have any informations about it?<br>
<br>
Gocus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/uuumdaien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uumdaien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(10/22/02 4:04:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Our pet spell at 55 summons a level 58 pet, that starts with weapons and dual wields / tripple attacks. Has good atk/ac (htis for 59 max) but still like 2k hp. At low health he will Enrage and he also will /shield you. Expect this to be gone soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/uezenofhom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezen ofHoM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(10/22/02 6:08:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.bigpond.com/jaym12/drings2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1>  Also pets regen is god like. 5% per tick. I was soloing in ME with him yesterday. Slow mob on pull let pet take over, no regent rune him and when pet at 10% HP mezz mob. By the time mezz wore off pet was 100%hp again and still had agro.God I hope this is not nerfed...first time i really have been able to solo effectivly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alerutheenchanter>Aleru the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(10/23/02 2:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> I was very surprised by this pet.<br>
<br>
It was the first time I've been able to solo in Velks without dying.  All pets since this have been pathetic &quot;farming greens&quot; uses, this pet can be used for xp purposes.<br>
<br>
The pet hits for 59 max, and the eraging doesn't seem to be anything brilliant (since the mobs is slowed anyway).  The pet is still fragile hpwise, but managable.  The regen is fast - very fast.<br>
<br>
Given that charm soloing is impossible past 50 (unless you intend to go backwards in levels), I think this is a great improvement for our pet.  It is similar to the pets of mages/necros, but is weaker then the mage epic pet.<br>
<br>
If the spell isn't changed, I might go explore some of those infrequented Luclin zones that mages soloers love.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, pre 22/10 Zumaik's was designed with pipsqweak mobs in mind and isn't at all useful for xp.<br>
<br>
I doubt that this pet will remain though, only the other classes (wiz/druid/necro/mage) are intended to solo past 50.  Unless you can DC of course, but first you need to get the xp &amp; aaxp....<br>
<br>
Aleru,<br>
Lvl 58 Chanter,<br>
Brell. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sugarpiehoneybunch>Sugarpie Honeybunch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(10/23/02 4:13:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> I knew it was too good to last.  I logged in yesterday and all I can cast is a light blue pet now.<br>
